Same here.  Here's the script for a git-aware bash prompt if anyone else is interested.<p>function parse_git_dirty {<p><pre><code>  [[ $(git status 2> /dev/null | tail -n1) != "nothing to commit (working directory clean)" ]] && echo "*"
</code></pre>
}<p>function parse_git_branch {<p><pre><code>  git branch --no-color 2> /dev/null | sed -e '/^[^*]/d' -e "s/* \(.*\)/ \1$(parse_git_dirty)/"
</code></pre>
}<p>PS1='[\w$(parse_git_branch)] '
